        "text": "Settlement adjustments are apportionments of ongoing property costs between the seller and the buyer as at the settlement date. Costs such as council rates, water rates, and body corporate levies are typically pre-paid for a quarter or a year. At settlement, the amount already paid by the seller that relates to the period after settlement is reimbursed by the buyer. The adjustment ensures each party pays only for their period of ownership."
      }
